{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I thought I would think about changing your perspective on the world a bit,"},{"time":4000,"text":"and showing you some of the designs that we have in nature."},{"time":7000,"text":"And so, I have my first slide to talk about"},{"time":11000,"text":"the dawning of the universe and what I call"},{"time":14000,"text":"the cosmic scene investigation, that is, looking at"},{"time":16000,"text":"the relics of creation and inferring what happened at the beginning,"},{"time":20000,"text":"and then following it up and trying to understand it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23000,"text":"And so one of the questions that I asked you is,"},{"time":25000,"text":"when you look around, what do you see?"},{"time":27000,"text":"Well, you see this space that's created by designers"},{"time":31000,"text":"and by the work of people, but what you actually see"},{"time":35000,"text":"is a lot of material that was already here,"},{"time":37000,"text":"being reshaped in a certain form."},{"time":39000,"text":"And so the question is: how did that material get here?"},{"time":42000,"text":"How did it get into the form that it had before it got reshaped, and so forth?"},{"time":45000,"text":"It's a question of what's the continuity?"},{"time":48000,"text":"So one of the things I look at is,"},{"time":50000,"text":"how did the universe begin and shape?"},{"time":52000,"text":"What was the whole process in the creation and the evolution of the universe"},{"time":56000,"text":"to getting to the point that we have these kinds of materials?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":58000,"text":"So that's sort of the part, and let me move on then and show you"},{"time":62000,"text":"the Hubble Ultra Deep Field."},{"time":64000,"text":"If you look at this picture,"},{"time":66000,"text":"what you will see is a lot of dark with some light objects in it."},{"time":70000,"text":"And everything but -- four of these light objects are stars,"},{"time":72000,"text":"and you can see them there -- little pluses."},{"time":74000,"text":"This is a star, this is a star, everything else is a galaxy, OK?"},{"time":79000,"text":"So there's a couple of thousand galaxies"},{"time":81000,"text":"you can see easily with your eye in here."},{"time":84000,"text":"And when I look out at particularly this galaxy,"},{"time":86000,"text":"which looks a lot like ours, I wonder if there's"},{"time":88000,"text":"an art design college conference going on,"},{"time":91000,"text":"and intelligent beings there are thinking about, you know,"},{"time":94000,"text":"what designs they might do, and there might be a few cosmologists"},{"time":97000,"text":"trying to understand where the universe itself came from,"},{"time":99000,"text":"and there might even be some in that galaxy looking at ours"},{"time":101000,"text":"trying to figure out what's going on over here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":103000,"text":"But there's a lot of other galaxies, and some are nearby,"},{"time":106000,"text":"and they're kind of the color of the Sun,"},{"time":107000,"text":"and some are further away and they're a little bluer, and so forth."},{"time":110000,"text":"But one of the questions is -- this should be, to you --"},{"time":114000,"text":"how come there are so many galaxies?"},{"time":116000,"text":"Because this represents a very clean fraction of the sky."},{"time":118000,"text":"This is only 1,000 galaxies."},{"time":120000,"text":"We think there's on the order -- visible to the Hubble Space Telescope,"},{"time":123000,"text":"if you had the time to scan it around --"},{"time":125000,"text":"about 100 billion galaxies. Right?"},{"time":127000,"text":"It's a very large number of galaxies."},{"time":129000,"text":"And that's roughly how many stars there are in our own galaxy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132000,"text":"But when you look at some of these regions like this, you'll see"},{"time":134000,"text":"more galaxies than stars, which is kind of a conundrum."},{"time":137000,"text":"So the question should come to your mind is, what kind of design, you know,"},{"time":143000,"text":"what kind of creative process and what kind of design"},{"time":145000,"text":"produced the world like that?"},{"time":147000,"text":"And then I'm going to show you it's actually a lot more complicated."},{"time":149000,"text":"We're going to try and follow it up."},{"time":151000,"text":"We have a tool that actually helps us out in this study,"},{"time":154000,"text":"and that's the fact that the universe is so incredibly big"},{"time":157000,"text":"that it's a time machine, in a certain sense."},{"time":160000,"text":"We draw this set of nested spheres cut away so you see it."},{"time":163000,"text":"Put the Earth at the center of the nested spheres,"},{"time":165000,"text":"just because that's where we're making observations."},{"time":167000,"text":"And the moon is only two seconds away, so if you take a picture of the moon"},{"time":170000,"text":"using ordinary light, it's the moon two seconds ago, and who cares."},{"time":173000,"text":"Two seconds is like the present."},{"time":175000,"text":"The Sun is eight minutes ago. That's not such a big deal, right,"},{"time":178000,"text":"unless there's solar flares coming then you want to get out the way."},{"time":180000,"text":"You'd like to have a little advance warning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":182000,"text":"But you get out to Jupiter and it's 40 minutes away. It's a problem."},{"time":185000,"text":"You hear about Mars, it's a problem communicating to Mars"},{"time":187000,"text":"because it takes light long enough to go there."},{"time":190000,"text":"But if you look out to the nearest set of stars,"},{"time":193000,"text":"to the nearest 40 or 50 stars, it's about 10 years."},{"time":196000,"text":"So if you take a picture of what's going on, it's 10 years ago."},{"time":199000,"text":"But you go and look to the center of the galaxy,"},{"time":201000,"text":"it's thousands of years ago."},{"time":202000,"text":"If you look at Andromeda, which is the nearest big galaxy,"},{"time":205000,"text":"and it's two million years ago."},{"time":206000,"text":"If you took a picture of the Earth two million years ago,"},{"time":208000,"text":"there'd be no evidence of humans at all,"},{"time":210000,"text":"because we don't think there were humans yet."},{"time":212000,"text":"I mean, it just gives you the scale."},{"time":214000,"text":"With the Hubble Space Telescope, we're looking at"},{"time":216000,"text":"hundreds of millions of years to a billion years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218000,"text":"But if we were capable to come up with an idea of how to look even further --"},{"time":223000,"text":"there's some things even further,"},{"time":224000,"text":"and that was what I did in a lot of my work,"},{"time":226000,"text":"was to develop the techniques -- we could look out back to even earlier"},{"time":230000,"text":"epochs before there were stars and before there were galaxies,"},{"time":232000,"text":"back to when the universe was hot and dense and very different."},{"time":236000,"text":"And so that's the sort of sequence,"},{"time":238000,"text":"and so I have a more artistic impression of this."},{"time":240000,"text":"There's the galaxy in the middle, which is the Milky Way,"},{"time":243000,"text":"and around that are the Hubble -- you know, nearby kind of galaxies,"},{"time":246000,"text":"and there's a sphere that marks the different times."},{"time":248000,"text":"And behind that are some more modern galaxies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250000,"text":"You see the whole big picture?"},{"time":252000,"text":"The beginning of time is funny -- it's on the outside, right?"},{"time":255000,"text":"And then there's a part of the universe we can't see"},{"time":257000,"text":"because it's so dense and so hot, light can't escape."},{"time":260000,"text":"It's like you can't see to the center of the Sun;"},{"time":262000,"text":"you have to use other techniques to know what's going on inside the Sun."},{"time":265000,"text":"But you can see the edge of the Sun,"},{"time":266000,"text":"and the universe gets that way, and you can see that."},{"time":268000,"text":"And then you see this sort of model area around the outside,"},{"time":272000,"text":"and that is the radiation coming from the Big Bang,"},{"time":275000,"text":"which is actually incredibly uniform."},{"time":277000,"text":"The universe is almost a perfect sphere,"},{"time":279000,"text":"but there are these very tiny variations"},{"time":281000,"text":"which we show here in great exaggeration."},{"time":284000,"text":"And from them in the time sequence we're going to have to go"},{"time":288000,"text":"from these tiny variations to these irregular galaxies and first stars"},{"time":292000,"text":"to these more advanced galaxies, and eventually the solar system, and so forth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296000,"text":"So it's a big design job,"},{"time":299000,"text":"but we'll see about how things are going on."},{"time":301000,"text":"So the way these measurements were done,"},{"time":303000,"text":"there's been a set of satellites, and this is where you get to see."},{"time":306000,"text":"So there was the COBE satellite, which was launched in 1989,"},{"time":310000,"text":"and we discovered these variations."},{"time":312000,"text":"And then in 2000, the MAP satellite was launched -- the WMAP --"},{"time":315000,"text":"and it made somewhat better pictures."},{"time":317000,"text":"And later this year -- this is the cool stealth version,"},{"time":321000,"text":"the one that actually has some beautiful design features to it,"},{"time":325000,"text":"and you should look -- the Planck satellite will be launched,"},{"time":327000,"text":"and it will make very high-resolution maps."},{"time":329000,"text":"And that will be the sequence of understanding"},{"time":332000,"text":"the very beginning of the universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333000,"text":"And what we saw was, we saw these variations, and then they told us"},{"time":337000,"text":"the secrets, both about the structure of space-time,"},{"time":340000,"text":"and about the contents of the universe,"},{"time":342000,"text":"and about how the universe started in its original motions."},{"time":345000,"text":"So we have this picture, which is quite a spectacular picture,"},{"time":348000,"text":"and I'll come back to the beginning, where we're going to have"},{"time":350000,"text":"some mysterious process that kicks the universe off at the beginning."},{"time":354000,"text":"And we go through a period of accelerating expansion, and the universe"},{"time":358000,"text":"expands and cools until it gets to the point where it becomes transparent,"},{"time":362000,"text":"then to the Dark Ages, and then the first stars turn on,"},{"time":364000,"text":"and they evolve into galaxies, and then later they get to the more expansive galaxies."},{"time":369000,"text":"And somewhere around this period is when our solar system started forming."},{"time":372000,"text":"And it's maturing up to the present time."},{"time":375000,"text":"And there's some spectacular things."},{"time":377000,"text":"And this wastebasket part, that's to represent"},{"time":380000,"text":"what the structure of space-time itself is doing during this period."},{"time":382000,"text":"And so this is a pretty weird model, right?"},{"time":386000,"text":"What kind of evidence do we have for that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":388000,"text":"So let me show you some of nature's patterns"},{"time":391000,"text":"that are the result of this."},{"time":392000,"text":"I always think of space-time as being the real substance of space,"},{"time":396000,"text":"and the galaxies and the stars just like the foam on the ocean."},{"time":401000,"text":"It's a marker of where the interesting waves are and whatever went on."},{"time":405000,"text":"So here is the Sloan Digital Sky Survey showing the location of a million galaxies."},{"time":411000,"text":"So there's a dot on here for every galaxy."},{"time":413000,"text":"They go out and point a telescope at the sky, take a picture,"},{"time":416000,"text":"identify what are stars and throw them away, look at the galaxies,"},{"time":419000,"text":"estimate how far away they are, and plot them up."},{"time":422000,"text":"And just put radially they're going out that way."},{"time":424000,"text":"And you see these structures, this thing we call the Great Wall,"},{"time":427000,"text":"but there are voids and those kinds of stuff, and they kind of fade out"},{"time":430000,"text":"because the telescope isn't sensitive enough to do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":432000,"text":"Now I'm going to show you this in 3D."},{"time":435000,"text":"What happens is, you take pictures"},{"time":436000,"text":"as the Earth rotates, you get a fan across the sky."},{"time":439000,"text":"There are some places you can't look because of our own galaxy,"},{"time":441000,"text":"or because there are no telescopes available to do it."},{"time":445000,"text":"So the next picture shows you the three-dimensional version of this rotating around."},{"time":449000,"text":"Do you see the fan-like scans made across the sky?"},{"time":452000,"text":"Remember, every spot on here is a galaxy, and you see the galaxies,"},{"time":458000,"text":"you know, sort of in our neighborhood, and you sort of see the structure."},{"time":462000,"text":"And you see this thing we call the Great Wall,"},{"time":464000,"text":"and you see the complicated structure, and you see these voids."},{"time":467000,"text":"There are places where there are no galaxies and there are places"},{"time":469000,"text":"where there are thousands of galaxies clumped together, right."},{"time":472000,"text":"So there's an interesting pattern,"},{"time":474000,"text":"but we don't have enough data here to actually see the pattern."},{"time":476000,"text":"We only have a million galaxies, right?"},{"time":478000,"text":"So we're keeping, like, a million balls in the air"},{"time":480000,"text":"but, what's going on?"},{"time":482000,"text":"There's another survey which is very similar to this,"},{"time":484000,"text":"called the Two-degree Field of View Galaxy Redshift Survey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":490000,"text":"Now we're going to fly through it at warp a million."},{"time":493000,"text":"And every time there's a galaxy -- at its location there's a galaxy --"},{"time":497000,"text":"and if we know anything about the galaxy, which we do,"},{"time":499000,"text":"because there's a redshift measurement and everything,"},{"time":501000,"text":"you put in the type of galaxy and the color,"},{"time":503000,"text":"so this is the real representation."},{"time":505000,"text":"And when you're in the middle of the galaxies"},{"time":506000,"text":"it's hard to see the pattern; it's like being in the middle of life."},{"time":509000,"text":"It's hard to see the pattern in the middle of the audience,"},{"time":510000,"text":"it's hard to see the pattern of this."},{"time":512000,"text":"So we're going to go out and swing around and look back at this."},{"time":517000,"text":"And you'll see, first, the structure of the survey,"},{"time":521000,"text":"and then you'll start seeing the structure of the galaxies"},{"time":524000,"text":"that we see out there."},{"time":530000,"text":"So again, you can see the extension of this Great Wall of galaxies showing up here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533000,"text":"But you can see the voids,"},{"time":535000,"text":"you can see the complicated structure, and you say,"},{"time":539000,"text":"well, how did this happen?"},{"time":541000,"text":"Suppose you're the cosmic designer."},{"time":543000,"text":"How are you going to put galaxies out there in a pattern like that?"},{"time":545000,"text":"It's not just throwing them out at random."},{"time":547000,"text":"There's a more complicated process going on here."},{"time":549000,"text":"How are you going to end up doing that?"},{"time":551000,"text":"And so now we're in for some serious play."},{"time":554000,"text":"That is, we have to seriously play God,"},{"time":556000,"text":"not just change people's lives, but make the universe, right."},{"time":559000,"text":"So if that's your responsibility, how are you going to do that?"},{"time":562000,"text":"What's the kind of technique?"},{"time":563000,"text":"What's the kind of thing you're going to do?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":565000,"text":"So I'm going to show you the results of a very large-scale simulation"},{"time":569000,"text":"of what we think the universe might be like, using, essentially,"},{"time":573000,"text":"some of the play principles and some of the design principles that,"},{"time":576000,"text":"you know, humans have labored so hard to pick up,"},{"time":579000,"text":"but apparently nature knew how to do at the beginning."},{"time":582000,"text":"And that is, you start out with very simple ingredients"},{"time":586000,"text":"and some simple rules,"},{"time":588000,"text":"but you have to have enough ingredients to make it complicated."},{"time":591000,"text":"And then you put in some randomness,"},{"time":595000,"text":"some fluctuations and some randomness,"},{"time":597000,"text":"and realize a whole bunch of different representations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":600000,"text":"So what I'm going to do is show you"},{"time":602000,"text":"the distribution of matter as a function of scales."},{"time":604000,"text":"We're going to zoom in, but this is a plot of what it is."},{"time":607000,"text":"And we had to add one more thing to make the universe come out right."},{"time":611000,"text":"It's called dark matter."},{"time":613000,"text":"That is matter that doesn't interact with light"},{"time":614000,"text":"the typical way that ordinary matter does,"},{"time":616000,"text":"the way the light's shining on me or on the stage."},{"time":619000,"text":"It's transparent to light, but in order for you to see it,"},{"time":621000,"text":"we're going to make it white. OK?"},{"time":623000,"text":"So the stuff that's in this picture that's white, that is the dark matter."},{"time":626000,"text":"It should be called invisible matter,"},{"time":628000,"text":"but the dark matter we've made visible."},{"time":630000,"text":"And the stuff that is in the yellow color,"},{"time":633000,"text":"that is the ordinary kind of matter that's turned into stars and galaxies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":637000,"text":"So I'll show you the next movie."},{"time":639000,"text":"So this -- we're going to zoom in."},{"time":642000,"text":"Notice this pattern and pay attention to this pattern."},{"time":644000,"text":"We're going to zoom in and zoom in."},{"time":648000,"text":"And you'll see there are all these filaments and structures and voids."},{"time":652000,"text":"And when a number of filaments come together in a knot,"},{"time":655000,"text":"that makes a supercluster of galaxies."},{"time":657000,"text":"This one we're zooming in on"},{"time":659000,"text":"is somewhere between 100,000 and a million galaxies in that small region."},{"time":662000,"text":"So we live in the boonies."},{"time":663000,"text":"We don't live in the center of the solar system,"},{"time":666000,"text":"we don't live in the center of the galaxy"},{"time":667000,"text":"and our galaxy's not in the center of the cluster."}]},{"cues":[{"time":670000,"text":"So we're zooming in."},{"time":672000,"text":"This is a region which probably has more than 100,000,"},{"time":674000,"text":"on the order of a million galaxies in that region."},{"time":677000,"text":"We're going to keep zooming in. OK."},{"time":680000,"text":"And so I forgot to tell you the scale."},{"time":682000,"text":"A parsec is 3.26 light years."},{"time":685000,"text":"So a gigaparsec is three billion light years -- that's the scale."},{"time":688000,"text":"So it takes light three billion years to travel over that distance."},{"time":691000,"text":"Now we're into a distance sort of between here and here."},{"time":694000,"text":"That's the distance between us and Andromeda, right?"},{"time":697000,"text":"These little specks that you're seeing in here, they're galaxies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702000,"text":"Now we're going to zoom back out,"},{"time":706000,"text":"and you can see this structure that,"},{"time":709000,"text":"when we get very far out, looks very regular,"},{"time":711000,"text":"but it's made up of a lot of irregular variations."},{"time":714000,"text":"So they're simple building blocks."},{"time":716000,"text":"There's a very simple fluid to begin with."},{"time":718000,"text":"It's got dark matter, it's got ordinary matter,"},{"time":722000,"text":"it's got photons and it's got neutrinos,"},{"time":725000,"text":"which don't play much role in the later part of the universe."},{"time":728000,"text":"And it's just a simple fluid and it, over time,"},{"time":732000,"text":"develops into this complicated structure."},{"time":735000,"text":"And so you know when you first saw this picture,"},{"time":739000,"text":"it didn't mean quite so much to you."},{"time":741000,"text":"Here you're looking across one percent of the volume of the visible universe"},{"time":746000,"text":"and you're seeing billions of galaxies, right, and nodes,"},{"time":749000,"text":"but you realize they're not even the main structure."},{"time":751000,"text":"There's a framework, which is the dark matter, the invisible matter,"},{"time":754000,"text":"that's out there that's actually holding it all together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":757000,"text":"So let's fly through it, and you can see how much harder it is"},{"time":761000,"text":"when you're in the middle of something to figure this out."},{"time":763000,"text":"So here's that same end result."},{"time":765000,"text":"You see a filament,"},{"time":767000,"text":"you see the light is the invisible matter,"},{"time":770000,"text":"and the yellow is the stars or the galaxies showing up."},{"time":774000,"text":"And we're going to fly around, and we'll fly around,"},{"time":776000,"text":"and you'll see occasionally a couple of filaments intersect,"},{"time":779000,"text":"and you get a large cluster of galaxies."},{"time":781000,"text":"And then we'll fly in to where the very large cluster is,"},{"time":784000,"text":"and you can see what it looks like."},{"time":787000,"text":"And so from inside, it doesn't look very complicated, right?"},{"time":790000,"text":"It's only when you look at it at a very large scale,"},{"time":793000,"text":"and explore it and so forth, you realize it's a very intricate,"},{"time":796000,"text":"complicated kind of a design, right?"},{"time":799000,"text":"And it's grown up in some kind of way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":803000,"text":"So the question is,"},{"time":805000,"text":"how hard would it be to assemble this, right?"},{"time":810000,"text":"How big a contractor team would you need"},{"time":812000,"text":"to put this universe together, right?"},{"time":814000,"text":"That's the issue, right?"},{"time":817000,"text":"And so here we are."},{"time":819000,"text":"You see how the filament --"},{"time":821000,"text":"you see how several filaments are coming together,"},{"time":823000,"text":"therefore making this supercluster of galaxies."},{"time":827000,"text":"And you have to understand, this is not how it would actually look"},{"time":830000,"text":"if you -- first, you can't travel this fast,"},{"time":832000,"text":"everything would be distorted,"},{"time":833000,"text":"but this is using simple rendering and graphic arts kind of stuff."},{"time":839000,"text":"This is how, if you took billions of years to go around,"},{"time":842000,"text":"it might look to you, right?"},{"time":843000,"text":"And if you could see invisible matter, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":846000,"text":"And so the idea is, you know, how would you put together the universe"},{"time":852000,"text":"in a very simple way?"},{"time":853000,"text":"We're going to start and realize that the entire visible universe,"},{"time":858000,"text":"everything we can see in every direction with the Hubble Space Telescope"},{"time":861000,"text":"plus our other instruments,"},{"time":862000,"text":"was once in a region that was smaller than an atom."},{"time":867000,"text":"It started with tiny quantum mechanical fluctuations,"},{"time":869000,"text":"but expanding at a tremendous rate."},{"time":871000,"text":"And those fluctuations"},{"time":873000,"text":"were stretched to astronomical sizes, and those fluctuations"},{"time":876000,"text":"eventually are the things we see in the cosmic microwave background."},{"time":880000,"text":"And then we needed some way to turn those fluctuations into galaxies"},{"time":883000,"text":"and clusters of galaxies and make these kinds of structures go on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":886000,"text":"So I'm going to show you a smaller simulation."},{"time":888000,"text":"This simulation was run on 1,000 processors for a month"},{"time":892000,"text":"in order to make just this simple visible one."},{"time":894000,"text":"So I'm going to show you one"},{"time":895000,"text":"that can be run on a desktop in two days in the next picture."},{"time":899000,"text":"So you start out with teeny fluctuations"},{"time":901000,"text":"when the universe was at this point,"},{"time":902000,"text":"now four times smaller, and so forth."},{"time":905000,"text":"And you start seeing these networks, this cosmic web of structure forming."},{"time":909000,"text":"And this is a simple one, because it doesn't have the ordinary matter"},{"time":912000,"text":"and it just has the dark matter in it."},{"time":914000,"text":"And you see how the dark matter lumps up,"},{"time":916000,"text":"and the ordinary matter just trails along behind."},{"time":919000,"text":"So there it is."},{"time":921000,"text":"At the beginning it's very uniform."},{"time":923000,"text":"The fluctuations are a part in 100,000."},{"time":925000,"text":"There are a few peaks that are a part in 10,000,"},{"time":927000,"text":"and then over billions of years, gravity just pulls in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":932000,"text":"This is light over density, pulls the material around in."},{"time":935000,"text":"That pulls in more material and pulls in more material."},{"time":938000,"text":"But the distances on the universe are so large"},{"time":940000,"text":"and the time scales are so large that it takes a long time for this to form."},{"time":944000,"text":"And it keeps forming until the universe is roughly about half the size it is now,"},{"time":950000,"text":"in terms of its expansion."},{"time":952000,"text":"And at that point, the universe mysteriously starts accelerating"},{"time":956000,"text":"its expansion and cuts off the formation of larger-scale structure."},{"time":959000,"text":"So we're just seeing as large a scale structure as we can see,"},{"time":962000,"text":"and then only things that have started forming already"},{"time":965000,"text":"are going to form, and then from then on it's going to go on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":968000,"text":"So we're able to do the simulation, but this is two days on a desktop."},{"time":974000,"text":"We need, you know, 30 days on 1,000 processors"},{"time":977000,"text":"to do the kind of simulation that I showed you before."},{"time":980000,"text":"So we have an idea of how to play seriously, creating the universe"},{"time":986000,"text":"by starting with essentially less than an eyedrop full of material,"},{"time":991000,"text":"and we create everything we can see in any direction, right,"},{"time":996000,"text":"from almost nothing -- that is, something extremely tiny,"},{"time":1001000,"text":"extremely small -- and it is almost perfect,"},{"time":1006000,"text":"except it has these tiny fluctuations at a part in 100,000 level,"},{"time":1010000,"text":"which turn out to produce the interesting patterns and designs we see,"},{"time":1013000,"text":"that is, galaxies and stars and so forth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1016000,"text":"So we have a model, and we can calculate it, and we can use it"},{"time":1021000,"text":"to make designs of what we think the universe really looks like."},{"time":1024000,"text":"And that design is sort of way beyond"},{"time":1027000,"text":"what our original imagination ever was."},{"time":1029000,"text":"So this is what we started with 15 years ago,"},{"time":1033000,"text":"with the Cosmic Background Explorer -- made the map on the upper right,"},{"time":1037000,"text":"which basically showed us that there were large-scale fluctuations,"},{"time":1041000,"text":"and actually fluctuations on several scales. You can kind of see that."},{"time":1044000,"text":"Since then we've had WMAP,"},{"time":1046000,"text":"which just gives us higher angular resolution."},{"time":1048000,"text":"We see the same large-scale structure,"},{"time":1049000,"text":"but we see additional small-scale structure."},{"time":1052000,"text":"And on the bottom right is if the satellite had flipped upside down"},{"time":1056000,"text":"and mapped the Earth, what kind of a map we would have got of the Earth."},{"time":1059000,"text":"You can see, well, you can, kind of pick out"},{"time":1061000,"text":"all the major continents, but that's about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1064000,"text":"But what we're hoping when we get to Planck, we'll have resolution"},{"time":1066000,"text":"about equivalent to the resolution you see of the Earth there,"},{"time":1070000,"text":"where you can really see the complicated pattern that exists on the Earth."},{"time":1075000,"text":"And you can also tell, because of the sharp edges"},{"time":1077000,"text":"and the way things fit together, there are some non-linear processes."},{"time":1081000,"text":"Geology has these effects,"},{"time":1083000,"text":"which is moving the plates around and so forth."},{"time":1086000,"text":"You can see that just from the map alone."},{"time":1088000,"text":"We want to get to the point in our maps of the early universe"},{"time":1090000,"text":"we can see whether there are any non-linear effects"},{"time":1093000,"text":"that are starting to move, to modify, and are giving us a hint about how"},{"time":1098000,"text":"space-time itself was actually created at the beginning moments."},{"time":1100000,"text":"So that's where we are today,"},{"time":1102000,"text":"and that's what I wanted to give you \na flavor of."},{"time":1105000,"text":"Give you a different view about what the design"},{"time":1107000,"text":"and what everything else looks like."},{"time":1111000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":1112000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}